{"lemma": "فُوهٌ", "slug": "فُوهٌ", "root": "ف.#.ه", "root_slug": "ف-_-ه", "root_link": "/words/roots/ف-_-ه", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 3, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n34881"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%87%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "mouth", "fa": "دهان", "ur": "منہ", "tr": "ağız", "id": "mulut", "bn": "মুখ", "es": "boca", "fr": "bouche", "de": "Mund", "ru": "рот", "zh": "嘴"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "singular of أَفَاوِيه (ʔafāwīh)", "tags": ["form-of", "singular"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "alternative form of فُوَّة (fuwwa, “madder”)", "tags": ["alt-of", "alternative"]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "common plural of أَفْوَهُ (ʔafwahu)", "tags": ["common", "form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Back-formation from أَفْوَاه (ʔafwāh)"}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n34881", "headword_ar": "فُوهٌ", "root": "fwh", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhN", "text_ar": "فَاهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhN", "text_ar": "فِيهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA) and, accord. to the copies of the K,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwhapN", "text_ar": "فُوهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [or, as in the CK,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawohap", "text_ar": "فَوْهَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] but correctly ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw~ahapN", "text_ar": "فُوَّهَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famN", "text_ar": "فَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", all signify the same [i. e. The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mouth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (K, TA:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afowaAhN", "text_ar": "اَفْوَاهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K, TA,) pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwhN", "text_ar": "فُوهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, TA,) and as such its case is plain; as pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhN", "text_ar": "فِيهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", it is like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^arowaAHN", "text_ar": "اَرْوَاحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riyHN", "text_ar": "رِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as pl of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhN", "text_ar": "فَاهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", it is allowable as having"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for its original medial radical; but as pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw~ahapN", "text_ar": "فُوَّهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", it is anomalous: (TA:) and another pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afomaAmN", "text_ar": "اَفْمَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) said by some to be pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fum~N", "text_ar": "فُمٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fam~N", "text_ar": "فَمٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with teshdeed, of which an ex. occurs in a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fm", "text_ar": "فم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but some disallow this pl.; and accord. to some, (TA,) it has no sing. (K, TA) agreeable with rule, (TA,) for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famN", "text_ar": "فَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawahN", "text_ar": "فَوَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) with the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "movent by fet-h, or ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawohN", "text_ar": "فَوْهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in some copies of the S,] with the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "quiescent, on the authority of IJ; (TA;) the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h", "text_ar": "ه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is elided, and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "becomes a movent final, therefore it must be changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", because of the fet-hah preceding it, so the word becomes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fA", "text_ar": "فا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but a noun may not be of two letters whereof one is [the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "n", "text_ar": "ن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of] the tenween, (K, TA,) thus the passage is expressed in the M, but MF remarks that correctly we should say whereof one is the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) and therefore a hard letter is substituted for it, one similar to it in kind, which is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "m", "text_ar": "م"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for they are both labials, and in the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "m", "text_ar": "م"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a sort of humming sound ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hawiY~N", "text_ar": "هَوِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwiY~N", "text_ar": "هُوِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) in the mouth, [or rather in the nose,] resembling [the sound of] the prolongation of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K, TA:) [several similar disquisitions, added in the TA, respecting the change from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fwh", "text_ar": "فوه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fm", "text_ar": "فم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", I omit, regarding them as needless: what is said on this subject in the S, in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fm", "text_ar": "فم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", I have mentioned in that art.:] in the present art., J says that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "m", "text_ar": "م"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fm", "text_ar": "فم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a substitute for the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h", "text_ar": "ه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", not for the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fwh", "text_ar": "فوه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but this is a mistake: (IB, TA:) the dual of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famN", "text_ar": "فَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famaAni", "text_ar": "فَمَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famawaAni", "text_ar": "فَمَوَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, S, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famayaAni", "text_ar": "فَمَيَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the second and third of which are anomalous: (IAar, K:) of the second, which occurs in a verse of ElFarezdak, [and respecting which see the first paragraph of art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fm", "text_ar": "فم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] Sb says that it is used by poetic license. (TA.) In using it as a prefixed noun, in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA fuwhuhu", "text_ar": "هٰذَا فُوهُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", they deemed the combination of the two"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h", "text_ar": "ه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "s difficult in respect of utterance; therefore they suppressed the [radical]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h", "text_ar": "ه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thereof [in this case, and then in other, similar, cases], and said,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA fuwhu", "text_ar": "هٰذَا فُوهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw zayodK", "text_ar": "فُو زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ayotu faA", "text_ar": "رَاَيْتُ فَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayodK", "text_ar": "زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mararotu bifiY zayodK", "text_ar": "مَرَرْتُ بِفِى زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and when prefixing it to [the pronoun denoting] thyself, thou sayest,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA fiY~a", "text_ar": "هٰذَا فِىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and this thou dost alike in using it in the nom. case and in the accus. and in the gen., because the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw", "text_ar": "فُو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and is then incorporated [into the pronominal"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, and the like is said in the Msb:) and sometimes, though rarely, they did the like in other cases, when not prefixing it; for instance,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA", "text_ar": "فَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "occurs at the end of a verse of El-'Ajjáj, without an affix, in this case for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhaA", "text_ar": "فَاهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) ―         -b2-  In the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kal~amotuhu", "text_ar": "كَلَّمْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhu A_ilaY fiY~a", "text_ar": "فَاهُ اـِلَى فِىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I spoke to him, his mouth being near to my mouth,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fAh", "text_ar": "فاه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is in the accus. case as a denotative of state: (S, TA: *) or by reason of the derivative ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mukal~imFA", "text_ar": "مُكَلِّمًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] meant to be understood: or, as Sb says, it is an instance of one of the nouns that are put in the place of inf. ns., and it is not to be separated from what should follow it, so that you may not say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kal~amotuhu faAha", "text_ar": "كَلَّمْتُهُ فَاهَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[alone], for you tell of your nearness to the person, and that there is not any one between you and him: and if you will, you may use the nom. case, meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wah`*ihi HaAluhu", "text_ar": "وَهٰذِهِ حَالُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "this being his state"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (Sb, TA,) i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwhu A_ilaY fiY~a", "text_ar": "فُوهُ اـِلَى فِىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his mouth was near to my mouth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], the clause [following"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kl~mth", "text_ar": "كلّمته"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] occupying the place of a denotative of state. (TA.) ―         -b3-  The saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhaA lifiyka", "text_ar": "فَاهَا لِفِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Meyd, K, TA,) which is a prov., (Meyd, TA,) means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God make the mouth of misfortune to cleave to thy mouth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Meyd, K, * TA;) [but lit. signifies, only,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "her,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its, mouth"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2465}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to thy mouth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and is [likewise] an instance of one of the nouns that are used in the manner of inf. ns. expressive of imprecation, by reason of a verb not mentioned: Sb says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fAhA", "text_ar": "فاها"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is without tenween, meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA Ald~aAhiyapi", "text_ar": "فَا الدَّاهِيَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as is shown by the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "wadaAhiyapK mino dawaAhiY Almanuw\n                      \n                     \n                        ni yarohabuhaA Aln~aAsu laA faA lahaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Many a misfortune is there, of the misfortunes of time, which men fear, that has no mouth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "wherewith to bite]: (Sb, TA:) A'Obeyd says that its primary meaning is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God make the ground to be in thy mouth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that it is like the sayings"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bifiyka AlHajaru", "text_ar": "بِفِيكَ الحَجَرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bifiyka AlA^avolabu", "text_ar": "بِفِيكَ الاَثْلَبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Meyd;) and [hence] it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "disappointment"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[cleave]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to thee:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * Meyd:) a man of Belhujeym, (S, Meyd,) cited by A'Obeyd, (S,) addressing a wolf that sought to get his she-camel, (Meyd,) says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "faqulotu lahu faAhaA lifiyka faA_in~ahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        qaluwSu A@moriy^K qaAriyka maA A^anota HaA*iruhu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And I said to him,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fAhA lfyk", "text_ar": "فاها لفيك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for she is the youthful she-camel of a man who will give thee as a guest's entertainment that which thou fearest"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S, Meyd; but in the S, as IB has observed,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA_in~ahu", "text_ar": "فَاـِنَّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is erroneously put for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA_in~ahaA", "text_ar": "فَاـِنَّهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";) i. e. [who will entertain thee with] the shooting of arrows; (Meyd;) [by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAriyka", "text_ar": "قَارِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] he means"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaqoriyka", "text_ar": "يَقْرِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qiraY", "text_ar": "قِرَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~ayofi", "text_ar": "الضَّيْفِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) it is also said that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhaA", "text_ar": "فَاهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is metonymically used as meaning the dust of the earth, which is termed the mouth of the earth because it drinks the water; and it is as though the saying meant"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the dust be in thy mouth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Meyd:) Sh is related to have said, I heard IAar say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lifiyka", "text_ar": "لِفِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhFA", "text_ar": "فَاهًا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with tenween, meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God make thy mouth to cleave to the ground;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or rather,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ground to thy mouth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "lit., simply,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a mouth to thy mouth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and some say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAhaA lifiyka", "text_ar": "فَاهَا لِفِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", without tenween, as an imprecation meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God break thy"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fam", "text_ar": "فَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. thy"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "teeth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fam", "text_ar": "فَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is often metonymically applied, as is also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwh", "text_ar": "فُوه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saqaY fulaAnN A_ibilahu EalaY A^afowaAhihaA", "text_ar": "سَقَى فُلَانٌ اـِبِلَهُ عَلَى اَفْوَاهِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one drew for his camels the water when they came to it, while they were drinking;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "not having stored it for them in the drinking-trough: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jar~a fulaAnN", "text_ar": "جَرَّ فُلَانٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibilahu EalaY A^afowaAhihaA", "text_ar": "اـِبِلَهُ عَلَى اَفْوَاهِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one suffered his camels to pasture while going along"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by his driving them gently:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jr", "text_ar": "جر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: so says As: and so accord. to the A and other lexicons; but the author of the K, by an omission, has assigned the latter explanation to the former phrase. (TA.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lawo wajadotu", "text_ar": "لَوْ وَجَدْتُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilayohi faA kari$K", "text_ar": "اـِلَيْهِ فَا كَرِشٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adonaY TariyqK", "text_ar": "اَدْنَى طَرِيقٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) has [with other, similar, phrases] been explained in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kr$", "text_ar": "كرش"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw farasK HamirK", "text_ar": "فُو فَرَسٍ حَمِرٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Mouth of a horse that is suffering indigestion in consequence of his having eaten barley and so made it to stink"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is an appellation applied to him who has stinking breath. (TA. [An ex. of it occurs in a verse of Imra-el-keys cited in the TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hmr", "text_ar": "حمر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as in Ahlwardt's “ Divans of the Six Ancient Arabic Poets, ” p. 125; and differently in De Slane's “ Diwan d'Amro-'kaïs, ” p. 36 of the Arabic text.]) ―         -b7-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw juradK", "text_ar": "فُو جُرَدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Mouth of a large fieldrat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw dabFA", "text_ar": "فُو دَبًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Mouth of a sort of small wingless locust,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or perhaps correctly"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw dabaApK", "text_ar": "فُو دَبَاةٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mouth of a small wingless locust,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] are nicknames applied to a little man. (TA.) ―         -b8-  One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA fuD~u fuwhu", "text_ar": "لَا فُضُّ فُوهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May his teeth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "front teeth, not be broken."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saqaTa fuwhu", "text_ar": "سَقَطَ فُوهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His teeth fell out."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fD", "text_ar": "فض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]) ―         -b9-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maAta lifiyhi", "text_ar": "مَاتَ لِفِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "liwajohihi", "text_ar": "لِوَجْهِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He died upon his face; prone:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saqaTa liwajohihi", "text_ar": "سَقَطَ لِوَجْهِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He fell upon his face:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l", "text_ar": "ل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in both being used in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as it is in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xar~uwA liA^a*oqaAnihimo", "text_ar": "خَرُّوا لِاَذْقَانِهِمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(expl. in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xr", "text_ar": "خر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), &c.]. (A, K, TA. [The explanation in the TK, being somewhat ambiguous (though correct), has misled Freytag in this case.]) And [in like manner, using"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "li", "text_ar": "لِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ElY", "text_ar": "على"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kb~ahu A@ll~`hu", "text_ar": "كبَّهُ ا@للّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lifiyhi", "text_ar": "لِفِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", one of their forms of imprecation, meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God cause him to die:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prostrate him"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon his face;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kab~ahu liwajohihi", "text_ar": "كَبَّهُ لِوَجْهِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b10-  [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw~ahapN", "text_ar": "فُوَّهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwhN", "text_ar": "فُوهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; like which it has"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afowaAhN", "text_ar": "اَفْوَاهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for a pl.]       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwhN", "text_ar": "فُوهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also, having for its pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afowaAhN", "text_ar": "اَفْوَاهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and pl. pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afaAwiyhu", "text_ar": "اَفَاوِيهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) [which last is of very frequent occurrence,] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Perfume,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an odoriferous substance:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "substance, with which a perfume,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an odoriferous substance, is compounded"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prepared"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yuEaAlaju", "text_ar": "يُعَالَجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "); like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tawaAbilu", "text_ar": "تَوَابِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies things, or substances, with which sorts of food are compounded or prepared: (S, Mgh:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tawaAbil", "text_ar": "تَوَابِل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "seeds used in cooking"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with which food is compounded"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prepared"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yuEaAlaju", "text_ar": "يُعَالَجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") are also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afowaAhu AlT~iybi", "text_ar": "اَفْوَاهُ الطِّيبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) [the pl. and pl. pl. are now generally applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "spices,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "aromatics:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^afowaAhu", "text_ar": "الاَفْوَاهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the pl. mentioned above, signifies [the seeds called]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~awaAbilu", "text_ar": "التَّوَابِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what diffuse fragrance"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[I read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nawaAfiHu", "text_ar": "نَوَافِحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in my MS. copy of the K, pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAfiHN", "text_ar": "نَافِحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v., instead of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nawaAfiju", "text_ar": "نَوَافِجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jiym", "text_ar": "جِيم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), the only reading that I find in other copies of the K, regarding the latter as indubitably a mistranscription,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of perfumes,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "odoriferous substances:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the sorts,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of flowers; (K, TA;) thus says AHn; and in one place he says that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlAfwAH", "text_ar": "الافواح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what are prepared for perfume, of sweetsmelling flowers;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and sometimes they are of herbs, or leguminous plants: (TA:) and also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sorts,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a thing [app. of any kind]: (K:) and one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa mino A^afowaAhi AlTyb", "text_ar": "هُوَ مِنْ اَفْوَاهِ الطيب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afowaAhi Albuquwli", "text_ar": "اَفْوَاهِ البُقُولِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It is of the sorts,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the mixtures,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "compounds, of perfume,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of herbs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "leguminous plants:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:) but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwhN", "text_ar": "فُوهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is not applied to anything that is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~aArN", "text_ar": "عَقَّارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (AHeyth, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eqr", "text_ar": "عقر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)"}], "source_refs": ["K", "TA", "S", "IB", "IAar", "Msb", "Sb", "Meyd", "Mgh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}